					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Broken slab set up infront of the ruined temple of Chennakēśava.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to the 16th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Beginning lost. It seems to register a gift of money made to the god Chennakēśava by the Dommari community for the merit of the twenty four families of that community.</p>						

						</summary>
